  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed basement unit would provide substandard accommodation in respect of the outlook that would be experienced within the main habitable areas of the new unit to the detriment of the future occupiers amenity. The development is therefore contrary to D6 (Housing Quality and Standards)&amp;nbsp; of the London Plan 2021 and LP2 (Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure a contribution towards affordable housing fails to deliver the maximum reasonable amount of affordable housing and is therefore contrary to policy H4 (Delivering affordable housing) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP13 (Affordable housing) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policies T6 (Car Parking) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed front boundary treatment being a timber bin store, by reason of its size, design and location would result in an incompatible form of development, which would adversely affect the character and appearance of the host building and surrounding streetscene. As such, the proposal is considered contrary to policy D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach) of the London Plan (2021) and Policy LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character).&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of poor layout and inadequate space would result in the provision of inadequate and unsuitable cycle parking. As such the proposed development is contrary to policies T1 (Strategic Approach to Transport), T4 (Assessing and Mitigating Transport Impacts) and T5 (Cycling) of the London Plan 2021, policies LP42 (Walking and Cycling) and LP43 (Transport and Development) of the Local Plan 2033(2020) and the guidance contained within Hackney Transport Strategy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
